parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt can cause the belt to malfunction, leading to a lack of protection for the driver and passengers in the event of an accident, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt stops working
the belt does not retract or lock into place
the belt moves only partway
the belt makes a grinding or whirring noise
the belt buckle fails
the belt comes off the track
the belt does not secure properly to the vehicle.

the buckle comes undone
the belt does not secure properly to the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
even when the driver's foot is off the accelerator pedal
the engine races or revs high
the vehicle surges forward
the vehicle accelerates to high speeds
the vehicle is difficult to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sticking gas pedal can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and potentially serious accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The gas pedal feels stuck or sticky
the gas pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine racing or revving can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and potentially serious accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine revs high or races
the engine accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
the vehicle surges forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks and cracks in the fuel tank can cause fuel to spill out, leading to a fire hazard, and potentially causing accidents or injuries.

and cracked or melted fuel tank.
